						<summary>

						<p>This is fragmentary. It makes mention of the Vishṇu temple at Iḍaiyāṟṟumaṅgalam in Iḍaiyāṟṟu-nāḍu a division of <hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍikulāśani-vaḷanāḍu.</hi> This is probably an inscription <hi rend="bold">Rājēndra-Chōḷa I</hi>, ‘Pāṇḍikulāśani’ being surmised to be a surname of his father <hi rend="bold">Rājarāja.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
